4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Existing law does not specifically address where
6 the monies deposited into certain county funds are to
7 be maintained.
8 This bill would require the monies deposited in
9 both county law library funds and presiding circuit
10 judge's judicial administration funds to be maintained
11 in separate funds within the county treasury.
12 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
13 technical revisions to update the existing code
14 language to current style.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Relating to county law library and judicial
22 administration funds; to amend Sections 11-25-7 and 12-19-310,
23 Code of Alabama 1975; to require county law library funds to
24 be maintained in a separate fund in the county treasury; to
25 require presiding circuit judge's judicial administration
26 funds to be maintained in a separate fund in the county
27 treasury; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to
28 update the existing code language to current style.
