29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
30 Section 1. Sections 11-25-7 and 12-19-310 are amended
31 to read as follows:
32 "§11-25-7
33 Upon the establishment of a county law library under
34 the provisions of this chapter, each county shall have and
35 maintain a separate fund within the county treasury known as
36 the County Law Library Fund and may have a separate law
37 library fund for each law library in the county. The county
38 law library funds shall consist of fundsmonies appropriated by
39 the state, county, or municipal governments,; fundsmonies
40 collected under the provisions of law,; proceeds from the sale
41 of copies, books, and other materials, or received from
42 donations, gifts, grants, and funds other than those
43 appropriated, and shall be audited as other county funds are
44 audited. SaidA county law library fund may be used to match
45 grants for library purposes. Library funds may be used to pay
46 library personnel. All purchases by or on behalf of sucha
47 county law library shall be exempt from all State of Alabama,
48 county, or municipal sales, use, or other similar taxes."
49 "§12-19-310
50 (a) In addition to the docket fees now authorized by
51 law, additional docket fees shall be assessed in all circuit,
52 district, and municipal courts as follows:
53 (1) In civil cases in the circuit and district courts,
54 except child support cases and as further provided for small
55 claims cases, an additional docket fee of forty-five dollars
56 ($45) and in small claims cases an additional docket fee of
